Moonâ€ The night before and night of a full moon are my chances every month to capture this amazing event to share with you all. Unfortunately here in Connecticut and much of New England rain & clouds decided to crash the party during moonrise. Last night I went down by the shore in neighboring Madison, CT to see if the clouds would clear in time, but during moonrise it was a wild storm complete with a downpour and lightning. I was actually able to see the moon glowing slightly through my windshield during this for less than a minute before disappearing again in the dark storm clouds. After the heavy rain passed Mother Natureâ€™s fireworks continued and I instead focused on capturing them with my phone camera. I may actually post a cool image I was able to pull from this and share so keep an eye out. Since I didnâ€™t capture the moon I wanted to share this image of a previous Augustâ€™s Super Blue Moon in my hometown of Guilford, CT. I have to mention how ridiculous it is to see the posts showing an actual blue colored moon when promoting this â€œblue moonâ€ every year as it has nothing to do with its color and another ridiculous editing display by many. When it showed up in between thick clouds it was a shade of orange like it always is when it is rising above the horizon. As I got higher up the color faded into its more usual brighter self as it slipped perfectly in between the clouds. I love how the clouds around the moon provide extra elements and drama to the scene instead of just having the moon sitting solo in a clear sky. Like most of my moonscape images this was captured using my Canon R5 body + Canon RF 100-500mm lens (@500mm) which has become my go to rig. Also for any other photographers that ask for settings: ISO 1600, f7.1, 1/125 sec.
